Strengthening the implementation capacity by:
* Reformulating the government tasks, so also restructure of the government organization;
* Increasing the knowledge level and skills of public servants;
* Applying new methods, techniques and technologies, including ICT.

Diversification of the economy with its two key goals:
* distribution of the economic risk and
* creation of employment.
* information on statistical systems (the General Bureau for the Statistics, ABS);
* development and spatial planning (the National Planning Machinery);
* the knowledge sector (the Anton de Kom University of Suriname);
* Research and Development in the minerals sector (a National Minerals Institute);
* Research and Development for the forestry and the environment (a National Institute for the Forest and the Environment);
* certification of production processes and products (the Standards Bureau).

Private enterprises:
* National entrepreneurs for policy objectives distinguished into:
	* micro enterprises including the enterprises in the informal sector;
	* small and medium-sized enterprises;
	* cooperatives;
	* large enterprises.
	* Private foreign entrepreneurs including (large) multinationals.
	* Non-profit legal persons that participate in economic transactions.

